---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="BMI Explained: Whats a Healthy Weight for Your Height?" description="BMI explained — how to calculate it, what the ranges mean, and how to interpret your score for health assessment." keywords="BMI calculator, body mass index, healthy weight, BMI ranges, BMI formula, weight for height, BMI chart, healthy BMI">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Health</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="BMI Explained: What is a Healthy Weight for Your Height?" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 19, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Body Mass Index (BMI) is the most widely used screening tool for weight categories. While it has limitations, understanding your BMI gives you a starting point for conversations with healthcare providers about healthy weight management.</p>

      <h2>The BMI Formula</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">BMI = weight (kg) / height (m)²</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Imperial: BMI = (weight in lbs × 703) / (height in inches)²</p>
      </div>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> A person weighing 70 kg who is 1.75 m tall: BMI = 70 / (1.75 × 1.75) = 70 / 3.0625 = 22.9</p>

      <h2>BMI Categories (Adults)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Underweight:</strong> Below 18.5</li>
        <li><strong>Normal weight:</strong> 18.5 - 24.9</li>
        <li><strong>Overweight:</strong> 25.0 - 29.9</li>
        <li><strong>Obese Class I:</strong> 30.0 - 34.9</li>
        <li><strong>Obese Class II:</strong> 35.0 - 39.9</li>
        <li><strong>Obese Class III:</strong> 40.0 and above</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What is a "Healthy" BMI?</h2>
      <p>The "normal" range of 18.5-24.9 is associated with the lowest statistical risk of weight-related health conditions. However, BMI alone does not determine health. It is one data point among many that doctors consider.</p>

      <h2>Quick Reference by Height</h2>
      <p>Healthy weight ranges (BMI 18.5-24.9) for common heights:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>5'0" (152 cm): 47-58 kg (104-128 lbs)</li>
        <li>5'4" (163 cm): 49-67 kg (108-145 lbs)</li>
        <li>5'8" (173 cm): 55-76 kg (122-164 lbs)</li>
        <li>6'0" (183 cm): 62-84 kg (136-184 lbs)</li>
        <li>6'2" (188 cm): 65-89 kg (144-194 lbs)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Important Context</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>BMI does not distinguish between muscle and fat — a muscular athlete may have a "high" BMI while being perfectly healthy</li>
        <li>It does not account for age, sex, ethnicity, or body composition</li>
        <li>Some populations have different risk thresholds (e.g., WHO suggests lower cutoffs for Asian populations)</li>
        <li>BMI is a screening tool, not a diagnostic one — it identifies who might need further assessment</li>
      </ul>

      <p>If you are concerned about your weight or health, BMI is a useful starting point — but speak with a healthcare professional for personalised guidance that considers your complete health picture.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/bmi" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open BMI Calculator →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/tools/bmi" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Tool →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
